<LanguageData>
  
  <!-- EN: cochlear implant -->
  <CochlearImplant.label>人工耳蝸</CochlearImplant.label>
  <!-- EN: An installed cochlear implant. An external microphone transmits a sound signal to electrodes wrapped around the inner ear's auditory sensing nerves. The electrodes stimulate the nerves according to the sound, creating a sensation of hearing. It's not as good as a natural ear, but it's a lot better than being deaf. -->
  <CochlearImplant.description>已安裝的人工耳蝸。外部麥克風將聲音訊息傳遞到內耳聽覺神經的周圍電極。電極根據聲音刺激神經產生聽覺。效果雖然不如天然的耳朵，但總比耳聾好多了。</CochlearImplant.description>
  <!-- EN: a cochlear implant -->
  <CochlearImplant.labelNoun>人工耳蝸</CochlearImplant.labelNoun>
  
  <!-- EN: joywire -->
  <Joywire.label>樂絲晶片</Joywire.label>
  <!-- EN: An installed joywire implant. While it dramatically improves a user's mood, the blanket of happiness makes it hard to concentrate on anything real. Joywires are illegal on many worlds, and are known for destroying whole cultures. -->
  <Joywire.description>已安裝的樂絲晶片。雖然它大幅提昇使用者的心情，但幸福之餘使得注意力難以集中。樂絲晶片因為使文明崩潰而為人所知，在許多世界是違法的。</Joywire.description>
  <!-- EN: a joywire -->
  <Joywire.labelNoun>樂絲晶片</Joywire.labelNoun>
  
  <!-- EN: painstopper -->
  <Painstopper.label>止痛晶片</Painstopper.label>
  <!-- EN: An installed painstopper implant. While it does allow the user to accomplish more, it turns out pain has a purpose. When you don't feel it, you can get hurt really bad really easily. -->
  <Painstopper.description>已安裝的止痛晶片。雖然它能讓使用者承受更多傷害，但當你感受不到痛覺時，其實你已經身受重傷了，事實證明痛覺是有意義的。</Painstopper.description>
  <!-- EN: a painstopper -->
  <Painstopper.labelNoun>止痛晶片</Painstopper.labelNoun>
  
  <!-- EN: power claw -->
  <PowerClaw.label>動力爪</PowerClaw.label>
  <!-- EN: An installed power claw consisting of a mechanical hand with a hooked claw on each finger. It cuts deep, and it is strong enough to crush a skull like a hand crushes an egg. The claws can be retracted, making it as useful as a natural hand for non-combat tasks, however its overall ungainliness slows down movement slightly. -->
  <PowerClaw.description>已安裝的動力爪，每隻手指上帶有兇殘利爪。它能砍進深處，也能夠把頭骨當作雞蛋般碾碎。非戰鬥情況下利刃可以縮回，變回有用的天然手臂，然而其笨拙的操縱力會減慢其他工作。</PowerClaw.description>
  <!-- EN: claw -->
  <PowerClaw.comps.HediffComp_VerbGiver.tools.claw.label>爪</PowerClaw.comps.HediffComp_VerbGiver.tools.claw.label>
  <!-- EN: a power claw -->
  <PowerClaw.labelNoun>動力爪</PowerClaw.labelNoun>
  
  <!-- EN: prosthetic arm -->
  <SimpleProstheticArm.label>人工手臂</SimpleProstheticArm.label>
  <!-- EN: An installed prosthetic arm. While it lacks a neural interface, its complex arrangement of internal joints allows it to mimic natural movement quite convincingly. Still, it is inferior to a real arm. -->
  <SimpleProstheticArm.description>已安裝的人工手臂。雖然缺少神經接口，但排列複雜的內部關節，能夠完全模仿自然動作。不過仍然不如真正的手臂。</SimpleProstheticArm.description>
  <!-- EN: fist -->
  <SimpleProstheticArm.comps.HediffComp_VerbGiver.tools.fist.label>手掌</SimpleProstheticArm.comps.HediffComp_VerbGiver.tools.fist.label>
  <!-- EN: a prosthetic arm -->
  <SimpleProstheticArm.labelNoun>人工手臂</SimpleProstheticArm.labelNoun>
  
  <!-- EN: prosthetic heart -->
  <SimpleProstheticHeart.label>人工心臟</SimpleProstheticHeart.label>
  <!-- EN: An installed prosthetic heart. It contains an electric motor that pumps blood smoothly around the body. Users often report feeling tired, but it's better than the alternative. -->
  <SimpleProstheticHeart.description>已安裝的人工心臟。內含一個電動馬達，向全身輸送血液。使用者會經常感到疲憊，但有總比沒有好。</SimpleProstheticHeart.description>
  <!-- EN: a prosthetic heart -->
  <SimpleProstheticHeart.labelNoun>人工心臟</SimpleProstheticHeart.labelNoun>
  
  <!-- EN: prosthetic leg -->
  <SimpleProstheticLeg.label>人工腿</SimpleProstheticLeg.label>
  <!-- EN: An installed prosthetic leg. While it lacks a neural interface, its complex arrangement of internal joints allows it to mimic natural movement quite convincingly. Still, it is inferior to a real leg. -->
  <SimpleProstheticLeg.description>已安裝的人工腿。雖然缺少神經接口，但排列複雜的內部關節，能夠完全模仿自然動作。不過仍然不如真正的腿。</SimpleProstheticLeg.description>
  <!-- EN: a prosthetic leg -->
  <SimpleProstheticLeg.labelNoun>人工腿</SimpleProstheticLeg.labelNoun>
  
</LanguageData>